// External sync provider credentials (Trakt, SIMKL). TEMPLATE ONLY.
//
// The repo is PUBLIC, so the real client id/secret values must NEVER be committed. This tracked
// *.example file documents the seam; the owner (or CI) provides the real values one of two ways:
//
//   1. Local dev: copy this file to app/Config/ExternalSync.xcconfig (gitignored) and fill it in,
//      then pass its values through to the build (e.g. an xcodebuild override, or a wrapper that
//      exports them). Do NOT wire it via project.yml `configFiles`: a fresh clone / CI checkout is
//      missing the gitignored file and xcodegen would then fail. This mirrors the VortXEdge secret
//      precedent (empty default in project.yml settings.base + Info.plist $(VAR) substitution).
//
//   2. CI: inject each value at build time as an xcodebuild setting from a GitHub repo secret, e.g.
//        xcodebuild ... TRAKT_CLIENT_ID=xxxx TRAKT_CLIENT_SECRET=yyyy \
//                       SIMKL_CLIENT_ID=zzzz SIMKL_CLIENT_SECRET=wwww
//
// project.yml defaults every one of these to EMPTY under settings.base, so a build with no override
// ships with blank credentials. Blank credentials make the whole External Services feature a hidden
// no-op (TraktAuth.isConfigured / SIMKLAuth.isConfigured are false): the Settings section is
// invisible and no external network call is ever made. That dormant state is the shippable beta.

// Trakt application (https://trakt.tv/oauth/applications). Device-code OAuth flow.
TRAKT_CLIENT_ID =
TRAKT_CLIENT_SECRET =

// SIMKL application (https://simkl.com/settings/developer/). PIN/device flow.
SIMKL_CLIENT_ID =
SIMKL_CLIENT_SECRET =
